<p>The tone of your message should be respectful and supportive, avoiding overly formal or casual language.  Focus on expressing your sincere condolences and offering words of comfort rather than lengthy explanations or unsolicited advice. Remember, the goal is to offer solace and acknowledge the client's loss in a meaningful way.</p>
    

